Paper: hep-th/9303062

Date: 1993-03-10

Title: The Energy-Momentum Tensor in Fulling-Rindler Vacuum

Authors: Parentani Renaud

Comments: 9 pages, ULB-TH-15/92

Journal-ref: Class. Quant. Grav. 10 (1993) 1409-1416

The energy density in Fulling-Rindler vacuum, which is known to be negative"everywhere" is shown to be positive and singular on the horizons in such afashion as to guarantee the positivity of the total energy. The mechanism ofcompensation is displayed in detail.